The White House has announced staff changes in the East Wing. Jackie Norris, the Chief of Staff to the First Lady, has been appointed as Senior Advisor to the Corporation for National and Community Service. Susan Sher, a longtime colleague and friend of the First Lady's, has been promoted to Chief of Staff. The First Lady expressed gratitude for Norris' work on national service issues and stated that she will continue to work closely with her in her new role. Sher also expressed her appreciation for the opportunity to be of greater service to the First Lady and the Administration.